cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use mcp-bastion, please cite it."
title: "mcp-bastion: A Reliability & Security Proxy for the Model Context Protocol"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Gowthaman
    family-names: Arumugam
    email: agowthaman90@gmail.com
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Gowthaman90/mcp-bastion"
url: "https://github.com/Gowthaman90/mcp-bastion"
abstract: >-
  A client-agnostic reliability and security proxy for the Model Context
  Protocol (MCP). It provides self-healing connections with automatic
  reconnection, runtime tool-security (tool-definition pinning / rug-pull
  detection, poisoning inspection, and shadowing detection), and a
  compliance-mapped audit trail crosswalked to the NIST AI RMF and the OWASP
  Top 10 for LLM Applications. Measured on the vendor-neutral mcp-defense-bench,
  it covers 63% of the MCP attack surface (15.0 of 24 vectors) at zero false
  positives.
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - Model Context Protocol
  - MCP
  - MCP proxy
  - AI security
  - LLM security
  - tool poisoning
  - prompt injection
  - NIST AI RMF
  - OWASP LLM Top 10
